m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Orren the Bear

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Orren the Bear. The Bloodstone clan and the Balemoon clan bowed before me."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Fiahn the Ore Master

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Fiahn the Ore Master. I traded with the dwarves, and the weapons of the Fiahn clan were the best in the land."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Ajb the Sweet-Voiced

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Ajb the Sweet-Voiced. Wherever I went, wars ended and sworn enemies were reconciled."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Lille the Quick

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Lille the Quick. No enemy could escape me, I overtook them like a storm."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Ruhad the Bookreader

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Ruhad the Bookreader. No one could match my knowledge of books, or my skill in the art of war."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Inbalta the Fire-Haired

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Inbalta the Fire-Haired. My blood-red hair burned as bright as the fortresses of my enemies."

The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Kigven Goldenmare. My proud herds roamed the steppe, like ships in the sea, and no flaw could be found in them."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Aremora the Skyreader

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Aremora the Skyreader. The stars revealed their secrets to me, and gave me guidance as I led the Blackearth clan into battle."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Hegwart the Snake

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Hegwart the Snake. In the forests of Sarkoris, none could match my cunning, or my knowledge of poisons."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Aregau the Saint

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Aregau the Saint. I fought like a dragon on behalf of my clan, but in the end, I left the world behind and devoted myself to Pulura."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Hidd the Twin

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Hidd the Twin. My brother Hedd and I ruled the forest and the steppe, and we are as inseparable in death, as we were in life."

The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Dwidry Stormraven. The spirits spoke with me, and granted me power like no one has ever seen."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Hedd the Twin

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Hedd the Twin. My brother Hidd and I ruled the forest and the steppe, and we are as inseparable in death, as we were in life."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Angna the Spinstress

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Angna the Spinstress. I used my husband's hair to spin the string with which I strangled his murderers."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Gonnla the Wild Boar

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Gonnla the Wild Boar. My army was so vast, all the young grass in the steppe was trampled when they marched."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Gweirn the She-Wolf

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Gweirn the She-Wolf. I walked the paths of spirits, and they helped me to defeat the Howlingblood clan."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Eohan the One-Eyed

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Eohan the One-Eyed. I offered my eye as a sacrifice to the spirits, and they revealed my future. This is how I was victorious."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Ajfne Bloody Spear

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Ajfne Bloody Spear. I owned the fortresses and lands of the Stagheart clan, until I made the spirits angry."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Surna the Daughter of Spirits

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Surna the Daughter of Spirits. I was an orphan who took shelter at the temple, but the spirits gave me the strength to build my own fortress."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Vigdelly the Wayfinder

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt bears the following epitaph: "I am the mighty chief, Vigdelly the Wayfinder. I reached the end of the steppe, and there I built the houses of my clan, to the envy of Ustalav."

m_DisplayNameText.LocalisedValue: Funerary Dagger of Ailberije, Master of Iz

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The funerary dagger of a Sarkorian chieftain. The hilt is inscribed with the following epitaph: "I, Ailberije, Master of Iz, built the fortress of Iz in the lands of Sarkoris. There is no other fortress like it in all the world."

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +3 agile dagger has its {g|Encyclopedia:Reach}reach{/g} increased by 5 feet. It grants its wielder a +5 luck {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} on all {g|Encyclopedia:Stealth}Stealth{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Skills}skill checks{/g}, and the ability to cast displacement {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} once per day as a 5th level wizard.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A fine example of the elven smithing craft from Nazrielle, a court artisan who made a deal with the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This weapon is a +2 flaming anarchic agile dagger.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A fine example of the elven smithing craft from Nazrielle, a court artisan who made a deal with the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +1 ghost touch dagger grants its wielder the ability to cast bestow curse (curse of weakness) {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} once per day as a 7th level wizard.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This item came from the forge of Varrask the half-orc — court master, also known as the Wildfist.

__root.Comment: Давать бонус к стелсу и сник атаке +1д6, +4 кинжал

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +4 dagger grants its wielder a +5 {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Stealth}Stealth{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Skills}skill checks{/g} and increases sneak {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g} with any weapon by {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d6{/g} damage.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This dagger, retrieved from the bottom of the lake in Whiterose Abbey, once belonged to a young man from the Strocalle family, who was murdered at the order of King Irovetti.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +1 dagger grants its wielder a +3 dodge {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Armor_Class}AC{/g} and immunity to nauseated condition.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A self-defense weapon made for wizards.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +1 dagger grants its wielder a +4 insight {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Initiative}Initiative{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}rolls{/g} and +1 dodge bonus to {g|Encyclopedia:Armor_Class}AC{/g}. {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}Attacks{/g} with it deal additional 1d6 lightning {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: The blade is twinkling in the twilight, as if there were a lightning bolt inside it.

__root.Comment: Dagger +2, Confusion 3 rounds on strike (DC 15)	Dagger Evil Lantern

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +2 dagger has a chance to confuse enemy on a hit.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: Sometimes, the reflection of a grimacing face appears in the blade.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: Whenever this +4 mithral {g|Encyclopedia:Speed}speed{/g} dagger lands a hit, it imposes a -3 {g|Encyclopedia:Penalty}penalty{/g} to target's Will score for 1 minute.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This dagger's blade sparkles with a blinding light.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +5 undead bane dagger grants its wielder a +2 {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Injury_Death}death{/g} effects' DCs and {g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}saving throws{/g} against them, and deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d6{/g} positive {g|Encyclopedia:Energy_Damage}energy damage{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This dagger, sharp like a razor blade, emits a faint glow that turns into a bright cold light in the presence of the undead. Its thin blade is adorned with spirals. On its handle, a cryptic utterance from Pharasma's holy scripture is written in Elven: "Birth and death are written in the bones, but bones can be broken."

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +2 cold iron dagger has an increased {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical{/g} multiplier of ×3.

Whenever the wielder of this +2 cold iron dagger casts a {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} with force descriptor, it deals additionally 2 force {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g} per dice {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}rolled{/g}.

Once a {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}round{/g}, when this +1 dagger lands a hit on an enemy, it deals them 1 {g|Encyclopedia:Constitution}Constitution{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:AbilityDamage}ability damage{/g}. This power can't lower the target's Constitution {g|Encyclopedia:Ability_Scores}ability score{/g} below 5.
This +1 dagger adds +1 to the {g|Encyclopedia:DC}DC{/g} for all {g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}saving throws{/g} against {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spells{/g} from the Evocation school the wielder casts.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A primitive stone knife. Someone or something crudely hacked and sharpened this piece of purple rock to use it as a weapon.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: Whenever this +1 cold iron dagger confirms a {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical hit{/g}, the target becomes blind for 1 {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}round{/g}.

This +2 dagger grants the wielder an ability to use the Curse of Undead ability 3 times per day.\nCurse of Undead: All living enemies in a 30-foot area must pass a {g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}Will saving throw{/g} ({g|Encyclopedia:DC}DC{/g} 24) or start slowly turning into the undead. Each turn the affected creature takes {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d4{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Constitution}Constitution{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}. Positive energy and {g|Encyclopedia:Healing}cure{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spells{/g} hurt it, like it was undead.

This +2 dagger allows the wielder to make two additional {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attacks{/g} during a full attack {g|Encyclopedia:CA_Types}action{/g}. This effect doesn't stack with the effect of the haste {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g}.

This is a +3 cold iron dagger that was used in weird rituals and is still thirsty for blood. While the wielder of the dagger is in combat, each time someone dies, the dagger increases its potency. The wielder can use its power to make any {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} empowered, as though using the Empower Spell {g|Encyclopedia:Feat}feat{/g}. Each usage spends one potency.\nEmpower Spell: All variable, numeric effects of an empowered spell are increased by half including {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonuses{/g} to those {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}rolls{/g}.\n{g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}Saving throws{/g} and opposed rolls are not affected, nor are spells without random variables.

This +5 living bane dagger deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}4d6{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Damage_Type}piercing damage{/g} to bleeding enemies on a successful hit. In addition, whenever the wielder delivers a Coup de Grace, they gain a +2 morale {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} on {g|Encyclopedia:Attack}attack{/g} and {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage rolls{/g} for 1 {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}round{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A thin, remarkably sharp left-handed dagger, once wielded by the famous demon assassin Yozz. This dagger strikes true, and spares no one. It has already claimed many lives. According to the legend, this blade was crafted for Yozz by the Razor Princess herself — the demon lord Andirifkhu.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: Whenever the wielder of this +5 cruel bleed dagger lands a first hit against a new enemy, that enemy must pass a {g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}Fortitude saving throw{/g} ({g|Encyclopedia:DC}DC{/g} 30) or become vulnerable to {g|Encyclopedia:Damage_Type}Piercing damage{/g} for 2 {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}rounds{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: A curved, serrated right-handed dagger, once wielded by the famous demon assassin Yozz. The wounds inflicted by this dagger are rarely fatal, but cause agonizing pain, and a significant loss of blood. According to the legend, this blade was crafted for Yozz by the Razor Princess herself — the demon lord Andirifkhu.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: Each time the wielder of this +5 dagger lands a hit with it after hitting the same target with the Soft Cut dagger, the enemy suffers additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}2d6{/g} + STR modifier {g|Encyclopedia:Damage_Type}slashing damage{/g}. If this weapons deals {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g} against a prone or paralyzed creature first time in a {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}round{/g}, it deals double the weapon damage.

This +5 shock dagger grants its wielder a +5 competence {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} on {g|Encyclopedia:Use_Magic_Device}Use Magic Device{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Skills}skill checks{/g} and a +4 competence bonus on {g|Encyclopedia:TouchAttack}touch attack{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}rolls{/g}.

This +5 dagger deals 1 {g|Encyclopedia:Damage_Type}slashing damage{/g} instead of {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d4{/g} piercing {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}. However, when dual-wielded along with the Deep Rip dagger, Soft Cut activates its additional power.
This +5 {g|Encyclopedia:Speed}speed{/g} elder caustic dagger allows its wearer to cast poison breath {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} 3 times per day as a 20th level druid.
This is a +1 cold iron ghost touch weapon.

This is a +3 brilliant energy heartseeker weapon. This weapon can tear the soul of a living enemy: whenever it lands a hit, it deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d6{/g} force {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This weapon was once the seat of Finnean's soul. Now that the soul of the Sarkorian Pathfinder has left the weapon, it has fallen silent forever.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This item grants its wearer Deadly Magic ability. If the wearer already has Deadly Magic, it grants them two additional uses. In addition, once per day, whenever the wearer's health falls below 0, it is restored to a maximum. Can only be equipped by a Lich.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This vessel contains your soul. Anyone who touches the vessel will sense the dark, dangerous essence that lurks inside.
